Abstract: Gravitating shells lead to simple minisuperspace models of black hole formation by gravitational collapse of matter. These can serve as a prelude to canonical quantization. Until recently, such models were hampered by the fact that their action was guessed rather than derived by a consistent minisu-perspace reduction of a general action principle. This problem has now been solved by Hajcek and Kijowski. We interpret here their variational principle as a Dirac-ADM canonical action principle along a timelike foliation including the shell as a leaf. We use the matter action which includes all degrees of freedom of dust shells, and introduce the action of simple field shells. We then 
